    <td>
      <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
        <tr>
          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font">Advanced Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Rapid Fire Team T.W.D.N.S.</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.17)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=23767">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=10055">Jerry "Claxton" Hill Jr</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=10055&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Creatureless Cald. Tournament winner. 2nd place at Jacon 2002 invitational.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> June 4, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi:<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(767)">Bria</a><br>
(Starting: Any two non-universal relics from the same region)<br>
<br>
Good Ol&#39; <a href="javascript:card_browser(375)">Ash<a href="javascript:card_browser(377)">Gar</a></a><br>
(Starting: Boomstick, <a href="javascript:card_browser(390)">Flame Geyser</a>)<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(676)">Amanax</a><br>
(Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(392)">Syphon Vortex</a>)<br>
<br>
Creatures:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(476)">Ormagon</a> x2<br>
<br>
Relics:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(734)">Climbing Staff</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(383)">Heat Lens</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(386)">Scroll of Fire</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(678)">Abraxin&#39;s Crown</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(546)">Gorgle&#39;s Glasses</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(507)">Relic Stalker</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(650)">Mantle of Shadows</a> x1<br>
Boomstick x2<br>
Firefly Amulet x1<br>
Inhibitor Band x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(787)">Rayje&#39;s Sword</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(652)">Rayje&#39;s Belt</a> x1<br>
<br>
Spells:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(390)">Flame Geyser</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(392)">Syphon Vortex</a> x2<br>
Brushfire x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(550)">Wildfire</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(357)">Storm Cloud</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(498)">Thunderquake</a> x1<br>
Firefly x2<br>
Crushing Heat x3<br>
Fireball x2<br>
Equali<a href="javascript:card_browser(767)">Bria</a>te x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(648)">Resonate</a> x1<br>
<br>
Total : 42 Cards and 3 Magi.<br>
<br>
   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Bria:<br>
Usually get Boomstick and Heat Lens as starting cards. If you are playing against orothe or you fear storm of fishes get a Heat Lens and an Abraxin&#39;s Crown. use Heat lens to control your opponents hand while building up your own. Watch out for Warriors boots, Rayje&#39;s Belt, and relic destruction. If you have inhibitor band out don&#39;t worry so much about the universal relics in your opponents hand. Using your Heat Lens you should be able to predict your opponents next turn and controll it some. Stall with Bria as long as possible to fill your hand. Once you get an Abraxin&#39;s Crown you can play it to start burning your opponent&#39;s Magi. Try to save it in your hand until you know you can defeat their Magi. If their Magi has a lot of energy, you can use the Abraxin&#39;s Crown to Storm Cloud them down to 1 energy and then burn them to defeat. Bria is mostly a controle and stall Magi but if you can defeat an opponents magi with her do it.<br>
<br>
Good Ol&#39; Ashgar:<br>
Get Boomstick and Flame Geyser as starting cards.<br>
If you were able to draw a Scroll of Fire with Bria you will want to save it for Good Ol&#39; Ashgar or Amanax. If your opponent has a lot of large creatures in play then use the Scroll of Fire and Flame Geyser to clear the board or at least lessen the energy on those creatures. Usually a combonation of Wildfire and Flame Geyser can clear the board. Try to save the Boomstick for Amanax if you can. Don&#39;t forget that you can play Brushfire from your discard pile once per turn. This also means that you can cast it for free from your discard pile using Ashgar&#39;s effect when he is attacked. Again try and get a Heat Lens in play as soon as possible to start hand control again. Use Ashgars effect whenever you can to save on energy.<br>
<br>
Amanax:<br>
Get Syphon Vortex as staring card.<br>
If you have the Scroll of Fire, now is a good time to use it. You now have a few choices to make to net Amanax the most energy. For large creature swarms use Flame Geyser or Wildfire. For large creatures use Boomstick or Syphon Vortex. For single small creatures just use Brushfire from the discard pile. Think about how you can net Amanax the most energy per turn while burning your opponents creatures away.<br>
<br>
Basic Strategies:<br>
Use Gorgle&#39;s Glasses whenever you can to draw cards. If you can clear the board with a wildfire or Flame geyser while you have the Glasses in play then you will be able to draw lots of cards. This works extreamely well against Bograth. Use Ormagon to clear off creature swarms that you can&#39;t handle. The Equalibriate is for decks that depend on growing creatures. Use Boomstick or Syphon Vortex to clear out big creatures and use brushfire, Fireball, and  Crushing Heat to deal with smaller creatures. Save Wildfires for creature swarms. Use Firefly Swarm and Firefly Amulet to stop uncontrollable creatures from attacking. <br>
<br>
Watch out for:<br>
Discard decks, fast drawing decks, relic control decks. Although Akido can&#39;t take creatures from this deck it can however get rid of Abraxin&#39;s Crown rather easily with the use of Hubdra&#39;s Cube and Karak, so watch out for these cards. Your relics can also set an Akido deck off with the use of Cube and Karak so be carefull. Watch out for decks that can get large creatures quickly such as Paradwyn and Naroom. These are probably your worst match ups but with a little practice you should be able to hold up against these decks.<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
I have to give team Elysium some credit for this deck. Although I never saw their deck list I did hear of their idea for a creatureless cald deck. At first I thought it had to be some strange combo deck using multi regions but once we made our version we saw that straight burn and control is actually a verry strong deck type. Although the idea is not ours, this is a T.W.D.N.S. origional deck and our own version. Change the deck according to your environment and your play style and practice. Have fun and good luck.<br>
<br>
Jerry Hill Jr. (Claxton) Team T.W.D.N.S. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=23767"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23767" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
